claim.claim-text:
1. A method comprising:
providing a pre-paid card to an authorized user, the pre-paid card being issued by a service provider;
applying a load to the pre-paid card;
establishing a fee for usage of the pre-paid card for the authorized user to pay, the established fee being independent from the load applied to the pre-paid card;
setting a periodic fee based on the established fee to be paid by the authorized user to pay on a periodic basis; and
recording receipt of payment of the periodic fee in response the authorized user paying the periodic fee.

6. A method for improving credit of a cardholder of a prepaid card, said method comprising:
establishing a load account associated with the prepaid card;
applying a load to the account to create an available balance for the cardholder;
establishing a credit account associated with the load account;
establishing an initial credit balance to the credit account, the initial credit balance being established based on a fee for which the cardholder is to pay for use of the prepaid card;
collecting a minimum periodic payment from the cardholder to be applied to the credit account; and
in response to collecting the payment from the cardholder:
applying the collected minimum periodic payment to the credit account; and
updating a credit history of the cardholder.

11. A method for enhancing credit of a cardholder of a pre-paid card, said method comprising:
issuing a pre-paid card to a cardholder, the pre-paid card having a load account associated therewith;
charging the cardholder a fee for use of the pre-paid card;
establishing a credit instrument associated with the load account;
setting a credit balance to the credit instrument up to an amount of the fee;
billing the cardholder on a periodic basis for a portion of the credit balance;
determining whether the cardholder timely paid on the periodic basis for credit balance;
in response to the cardholder timely paying on the periodic basis for the credit balance, recording that the payment as being timely paid on the period basis;
otherwise, recording that the payment was not timely paid on the periodic basis; and
reporting timeliness of the payment of the portion of the credit balance, the timeliness of the payment being used to affect a credit score of the cardholder.

16. A method for enhancing credit of a cardholder of a pre-paid card, said method comprising:
issuing a pre-paid card to a cardholder, the pre-paid card having a load account associated therewith;
charging the cardholder a fee for use of the prepaid card;
establishing a credit instrument associated with the load account;
applying a portion of the fee to a credit balance associated with the credit instrument on a periodic basis;
billing the cardholder for a credit balance of the credit instrument, the credit balance being separate from a load balance of the load account used for purchasing goods and services;
determining whether the cardholder timely paid the bill for the credit balance;
in response to the cardholder timely paying for the bill, recording the payment as being timely paid;
otherwise, recording that the bill was not timely paid; and
reporting the timeliness of the payment, the timeliness of the payment being used to affect a credit score of the cardholder.
